{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Using Regularized Methods for Regression\n","\n","Regularization is a technique used to tackle **overfitting** by introducing a penalty against complexity. It works by adding additional information to the model, which shrinks the parameter values.\n","\n","The three most popular approaches to regularized linear regression are **Ridge**, **LASSO**, and **Elastic Net**.\n","\n","### 1. Ridge Regression (L2 Penalty)\n","\n","Ridge regression adds the squared sum of the weights (an L2 penalty) to the Mean Squared Error (MSE) loss function.\n","\n","**Loss Function:**\n","\n","\n","$$L(\\boldsymbol{w})_{Ridge} = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} \\left(y^{(i)} - \\hat{y}^{(i)}\\right)^2 + \\lambda \\|\\boldsymbol{w}\\|_2^2$$\n","\n","**L2 Term Definition:**\n","\n","\n","$$\\lambda \\|\\boldsymbol{w}\\|_2^2 = \\lambda \\sum_{j=1}^{m} w_j^2$$\n","\n","* **Key concept:** Increasing the hyperparameter $\\lambda$ increases regularization strength, which shrinks the weights. The bias unit ($b$) is not regularized.\n","\n","### 2. LASSO Regression (L1 Penalty)\n","\n","LASSO (Least Absolute Shrinkage and Selection Operator) can lead to **sparse models**. Depending on the regularization strength, certain weights can become exactly zero. This makes LASSO highly useful as a supervised feature selection technique.\n","\n","**Loss Function:**\n","\n","\n","$$L(\\boldsymbol{w})_{Lasso} = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} \\left(y^{(i)} - \\hat{y}^{(i)}\\right)^2 + \\lambda \\|\\boldsymbol{w}\\|_1$$\n","\n","**L1 Term Definition:**\n","\n","\n","$$\\lambda \\|\\boldsymbol{w}\\|_1 = \\lambda \\sum_{j=1}^{m} |w_j|$$\n","\n","* **Limitation & Advantage:** If the number of features ($m$) is greater than the number of training examples ($n$), LASSO selects at most $n$ features. While sometimes undesirable, this property avoids perfectly fitting \"saturated\" models, which fail to generalize.\n","\n","### 3. Elastic Net (L1 & L2 Penalty)\n","\n","Elastic Net acts as a compromise between Ridge and LASSO. It combines an L1 penalty to generate sparsity and an L2 penalty to allow for selecting more than $n$ features when $m > n$.\n","\n","**Loss Function:**\n","\n","\n","$$L(\\boldsymbol{w})_{Elastic Net} = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} \\left(y^{(i)} - \\hat{y}^{(i)}\\right)^2 + \\lambda_2 \\|\\boldsymbol{w}\\|_2^2 + \\lambda_1 \\|\\boldsymbol{w}\\|_1$$\n","\n","---"],"metadata":{"id":"0JUdlqyoD0a-"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Scikit-Learn Implementations\n","\n","In `scikit-learn`, the regularization strength hyperparameter $\\lambda$ is regulated by the parameter `alpha`."],"metadata":{"id":"y2PuV8HqFoOM"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Ridge Implementation"],"metadata":{"id":"MvwBQUKpFq7b"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge\n","\n","# Initialize Ridge regression with an L2 penalty\n","ridge = Ridge(alpha=1.0)"],"outputs":[],"execution_count":1,"metadata":{"id":"GIGY86gzD0bB","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781875633191,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1912,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}}}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### LASSO Implementation"],"metadata":{"id":"vNlQb-YgD0bD"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.linear_model import Lasso\n","\n","# Initialize LASSO regression with an L1 penalty\n","lasso = Lasso(alpha=1.0)"],"outputs":[],"execution_count":2,"metadata":{"id":"hsdks-NVD0bD","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781875633195,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}}}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Elastic Net Implementation\n","\n","The ElasticNet implementation allows you to vary the L1 to L2 ratio. Setting the `l1_ratio` to `1.0` makes the Elastic Net regressor mathematically identical to LASSO regression."],"metadata":{"id":"7bIkfF-XD0bE"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.linear_model import ElasticNet\n","\n","# Initialize Elastic Net combining L1 and L2 penalties\n","elanet = ElasticNet(alpha=1.0, l1_ratio=0.5)"],"outputs":[],"execution_count":3,"metadata":{"id":"GrfS6ml6D0bE","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781875633197,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}}}}],"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[]},"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0}